               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480403-name-946" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-946" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-946" type="surname" value="M'BETH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-946" type="given" value="CHARLOTTE"></interp>CHARLOTTE M'BETH.</persName>
                  </hi>—I am wife of William M'Beth, of Pimlico. On 23rd March, about one o'clock, I was in Strutton-ground—I had this bag (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>) twice round my wrist and once round my finger—it contained two purses, and about 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., in shillings and sixpences—the prisoner came up and took it violenly—he tore my glove and handkerchief, and made my finger very sore—he ran down Pear-street—I am sure he is the man.</p>
